Monday Jan 1923
My dear Nelson Antrim Crawford,
I trust you will forgive me that I cannot act in the short story matter.
In the first place my own conception is so at war with the popular magazine conception -- plot - surface - action etc. This [unclear] may want to make a living or study writing. Why [unclear] would not

Jan 1st 1924.

Dear Reds and Arthur - 

    If you are in the boat this winter I hope it is not as cool as it is here. A heavy snow storm lasting three days - deep snow over all the mountains, the fields white.

    I have at last got through the revisions of the long book on which I worked all winter and am into another now. A damn nice difficult elusive theme that I may pull off and may not.

    One of the most exciting books I've read for years is Cane by Jean Toomer - a negress. Just the feeling of the south

    Confidentially I hope to be back in the south in the late spring -  to New Orleans perhaps. May put in the summer there. It will be hot as hell but great stuff. If you remember we talked once of going drifting

in a  boat down in that country.

    Why don't you two manage to get off to the south in your boat next summer. Lordy what things you would get up the rivers and bayouts among the blacks. Damned if I don't think it would be a painting paradise for you both.

    Lots of love

    Sherwood.

33 E Liberty St.
Reno - Nev.

Dear Arthur + Red

    Elizabeth and I are going for a month's [set?] to California. I'm speaking a few times - to pay expenses.

    About May 1st we're going up to the farm - in south west Virginia.

    Better get me old Friend and drift down that way. Mighty sorry I'm not seeing the show in Stieglitz room, you, Hartley. O Keefe + Marin.

    My last book is selling -  a new experience for me.

    Love to you both

    Sherwood

[letterhead: The Marion Publishing Company, Marion, VA]
Dear Arthur - + Red

    No - I am away out west - in the mountains. It is nice here but I am thinking of prying loose. I expect that, within a few months I will be drifting about again.

    My son + I are running some country papers down here. I expect we will keep on running them - or he will - 

    I hope to God my drifting will send me your way

    Sherwood
